    <sec id="sec-methods">
      <title>Methods</title>
      <p>The workflow appears in <xref ref-type="fig" rid="fig-1">Fig. 1</xref>.</p>
      <fig-group id="fig-group-1">
        <fig id="fig-1">
          <label>Figure 1</label>
          <caption><p>System overview with two processing stages.</p></caption>
          <graphic xlink:href="figure-1.svg"/>
        </fig>
      </fig-group>
      <p>The objective is defined by <xref ref-type="disp-formula" rid="eq-1">Eq. (1)</xref>.</p>
      <disp-formula id="eq-1">
        <label>(1)</label>
        <alternatives>
          <mml:math xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mml:mi>L</mml:mi><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:mn>1</mml:mn></mml:math>
          <tex-math><![CDATA[L=1]]></tex-math>
        </alternatives>
      </disp-formula>
      <p><xref ref-type="boxed-text" rid="alg-1">Algorithm 1</xref> applies the update.</p>
      <boxed-text id="alg-1" content-type="algorithm">
        <label>Algorithm 1</label>
        <caption><p>Training procedure.</p></caption>
        <code code-type="pseudocode">Input: X
Output: theta
Initialize theta
for x in X:
  update theta
return theta</code>
      </boxed-text>
    </sec>
